799
00:49:16,721 --> 00:49:18,120
the authority
to... to build this?

800
00:49:18,122 --> 00:49:20,690
Oh, yeah, he thinks he does,
yeah.

801
00:49:20,692 --> 00:49:23,192
I mean, you know, I, um...

802
00:49:23,194 --> 00:49:26,195
I left my job, and I
moved my stuff here.

803
00:49:26,197 --> 00:49:27,730
If I don't really have a job...

804
00:49:27,732 --> 00:49:28,732
no, you have a job.

805
00:49:28,733 --> 00:49:30,633
I... I hired you.

806
00:49:30,635 --> 00:49:32,034
Uh-huh.

807
00:49:32,036 --> 00:49:34,303
I mean, usually, the
board hires me.

808
00:49:34,305 --> 00:49:36,605
I don't have a board.

809
00:49:36,607 --> 00:49:37,540
Should I get a board?

810
00:49:37,542 --> 00:49:40,009
Bruce, would you like
some more wine?

811
00:49:40,011 --> 00:49:41,544
Yes, please.

812
00:49:54,658 --> 00:49:57,593
Well, he seems very nice.

813
00:49:57,595 --> 00:49:58,761
Yeah.

814
00:49:58,763 --> 00:50:01,831
But do you think you could try
to remember to tell me

815
00:50:01,833 --> 00:50:04,967
the next time you invite
somebody over for dinner?

816
00:50:04,969 --> 00:50:07,470
I mean, I'm... I'm glad you
had someone over

817
00:50:07,472 --> 00:50:10,072
and that we had dinner together.

818
00:50:10,074 --> 00:50:12,274
[ Crickets chirping ]

819
00:50:20,050 --> 00:50:22,251
[ Bell tolling ]

820
00:50:23,820 --> 00:50:25,054
Lydia.

821
00:50:25,056 --> 00:50:26,822
John...

822
00:50:28,692 --> 00:50:30,826
Sorry about your loss.

823
00:50:30,828 --> 00:50:33,462
Well, thank you. Thank you.

824
00:50:33,464 --> 00:50:35,064
Uh,

825
00:50:35,066 --> 00:50:38,167
I was wondering if
you've heard about

826
00:50:38,169 --> 00:50:40,169
this project that
I'm working on.

827
00:50:40,171 --> 00:50:41,171
The hospital?

828
00:50:41,172 --> 00:50:42,638
Yeah. Yeah.

829
00:50:42,640 --> 00:50:45,641
Um, I was hoping

830
00:50:45,643 --> 00:50:48,844
that I could have your
support on it.

831
00:50:50,714 --> 00:50:55,217
Honestly, I don't think I can
be much help to you on that.

832
00:50:55,219 --> 00:50:57,686
The folks I have influence with

833
00:50:57,688 --> 00:51:00,389
are just too suspicious of you,
John.

834
00:51:00,391 --> 00:51:02,425
Sorry.

835
00:51:35,926 --> 00:51:37,093
You gotta be kidding.

836
00:51:37,095 --> 00:51:38,661
Really, it was awful.

837
00:51:38,663 --> 00:51:44,033
Apparently, dad talked this guy
into leaving a real job.

838
00:51:44,035 --> 00:51:45,234
Is this some kind of
cut-rate deck?

839
00:51:45,236 --> 00:51:47,303
Oh, listen to her.

840
00:51:47,305 --> 00:51:49,972
Whoa, don't bet outside
your comfort zone.

841
00:51:49,974 --> 00:51:51,273
I'll raise you. Okay.

842
00:51:51,275 --> 00:51:53,242
This guy, by the end
of the evening,

843
00:51:53,244 --> 00:51:54,543
he had this look on his face,

844
00:51:54,545 --> 00:51:56,278
you know, like the
environmentalists get

845
00:51:56,280 --> 00:51:58,447
when they realize that dad has
done a number on them?

846
00:51:58,449 --> 00:52:00,149
Sounds like the old dad.

847
00:52:00,151 --> 00:52:01,417
Yeah.

848
00:52:01,419 --> 00:52:03,719
Is he getting anywhere
with this hospital?

849
00:52:03,721 --> 00:52:04,620
Uh, whew.

850
00:52:04,622 --> 00:52:06,388
I... you know, I don't
really know.

851
00:52:06,390 --> 00:52:07,756
He doesn't talk to me about it.

852
00:52:07,758 --> 00:52:09,925
It's weird. He's normally
such a chatterbox.

853
00:52:11,595 --> 00:52:13,863
Well, it's good he
has a project.

854
00:52:13,865 --> 00:52:14,865
Yes, yes. Yeah.

855
00:52:14,866 --> 00:52:16,232
Yeah, yeah.

856
00:52:16,234 --> 00:52:17,933
Fantasy of some hospital

857
00:52:17,935 --> 00:52:19,201
so he can wipe out the memories

858
00:52:19,203 --> 00:52:21,036
of what happened to Maria
at the old one

859
00:52:21,038 --> 00:52:22,438
and, uh, forget the
family he has left.

860
00:52:22,440 --> 00:52:23,739
Michael. Okay, Michael.

861
00:52:23,741 --> 00:52:26,408
What? It's like none of
us even exist.

862
00:52:26,410 --> 00:52:29,545
Michael, everyone that loses
someone goes through this.

863
00:52:31,381 --> 00:52:33,716
We just have to stick together.

864
00:52:36,820 --> 00:52:38,420
Whose bet is it?

865
00:52:40,190 --> 00:52:42,725
Mine.

866
00:52:44,961 --> 00:52:46,996
[ Siren blaring ]

867
00:52:55,038 --> 00:52:56,438
Steph.

868
00:52:58,041 --> 00:52:59,575
You there?

869
00:53:22,065 --> 00:53:23,999
Needless to say, we
love the idea.

870
00:53:24,001 --> 00:53:25,501
We're... we're 100% behind it.

871
00:53:25,503 --> 00:53:27,369
It's a beautiful thing,
what you're doing.

872
00:53:27,371 --> 00:53:29,171
Especially with everything that
you've been through.

873
00:53:29,173 --> 00:53:32,575
Okay. What do you
need me to do?

874
00:53:33,810 --> 00:53:35,778
Well, the thing is...

875
00:53:35,780 --> 00:53:39,348
I'm not a patient you're
giving bad news to.

876
00:53:39,350 --> 00:53:41,550
It's all right. You can just...

877
00:53:41,552 --> 00:53:42,351
what?

878
00:53:42,353 --> 00:53:45,020
All right. Well, how do I...

879
00:53:45,022 --> 00:53:46,188
how do I put this? Um,

880
00:53:46,190 --> 00:53:48,390
despite everybody loving kids

881
00:53:48,392 --> 00:53:50,693
and how they're our... our
future and everything,

882
00:53:50,695 --> 00:53:56,065
uh, pediatrics is the bottom
of the food chain,

883
00:53:56,067 --> 00:53:57,399
neurosurgeons, the
transplant guys

884
00:53:57,401 --> 00:53:59,368
being the big guns around here

885
00:53:59,370 --> 00:54:00,736
since they bring in the money.

886
00:54:00,738 --> 00:54:02,805
Now, they are not happy
with your idea,

887
00:54:02,807 --> 00:54:05,374
because they're like, "well,
we want a new toy.

888
00:54:05,376 --> 00:54:06,809
"We want a gamma knife.

889
00:54:06,811 --> 00:54:08,911
We don't want a
children's hospital."

890
00:54:08,913 --> 00:54:12,181
So they've gone to bitch to all
of their friends at the
county legislature,

891
00:54:12,183 --> 00:54:13,549
who unfortunately
are our bosses,

892
00:54:13,551 --> 00:54:15,751
and they're not happy with
your idea either,

893
00:54:15,753 --> 00:54:17,486
because they don't
want to take on

894
00:54:17,488 --> 00:54:19,088
any big capital projects during
an election cycle.

895
00:54:19,090 --> 00:54:21,757
Their biggest donors, who don't
want to lose any business,

896
00:54:21,759 --> 00:54:23,826
they don't want you stealing
any of their business...

897
00:54:23,828 --> 00:54:25,527
[ Overlapping ] ...State
board of health

898
00:54:25,529 --> 00:54:27,429
which has to approve any
construction of new hospitals.

899
00:54:27,431 --> 00:54:29,265
They don't want you taking
their business.

900
00:54:29,267 --> 00:54:31,166
And a lot of these s. O.B.S...

901
00:54:31,168 --> 00:54:32,534
construction on a new hospital.

902
00:54:32,536 --> 00:54:33,736
Did I leave anything out?

903
00:54:33,738 --> 00:54:36,105
Money.

904
00:54:36,107 --> 00:54:39,575
Yeah, nobody's mentioned where
would the money come from.

905
00:54:39,577 --> 00:54:42,244
Okay. We finished?

906
00:54:42,246 --> 00:54:43,412
That's not enough?

907
00:54:43,414 --> 00:54:45,447
Bruce found a fund-raiser.

908
00:54:45,449 --> 00:54:47,449
I'll speak to the state senator.

909
00:54:47,451 --> 00:54:49,752
It's all good.

910
00:54:54,557 --> 00:54:57,593
Courage, compassion, devotion,
destiny.

911
00:54:58,395 --> 00:55:01,330
What do you think?

912
00:55:01,332 --> 00:55:04,233
It's wonderful, Michael.

913
00:55:05,302 --> 00:55:07,369
It's so big.

914
00:55:07,371 --> 00:55:09,505
That must have hurt quite a lot.

915
00:55:09,507 --> 00:55:11,373
Lot less than laying around,
trying to figure out

916
00:55:11,375 --> 00:55:13,642
how long it would take to
flunk out. Heh.

917
00:55:13,644 --> 00:55:15,544
I'm gonna go for a walk.

918
00:55:23,253 --> 00:55:24,687
[ Sighs ]

919
00:55:24,689 --> 00:55:26,388
I'm trying to take care of him.

920
00:55:26,390 --> 00:55:28,657
I know. I know you are.

921
00:55:28,659 --> 00:55:30,459
At least I've got my classes

922
00:55:30,461 --> 00:55:32,861
to get my mind off things,
but he's...

923
00:55:38,768 --> 00:55:41,203
did you ever try to talk to
dad about things?

924
00:55:41,205 --> 00:55:43,639
Dad?

925
00:55:43,641 --> 00:55:47,643
I just have to be strong for
him until he comes out of it.

926
00:55:47,645 --> 00:55:51,747
Yeah, but what if he doesn't?

927
00:55:51,749 --> 00:55:53,015
He will.

928
00:55:53,017 --> 00:55:54,783
I know he will.

929
00:55:56,052 --> 00:55:59,254
It's just weird.

930
00:55:59,256 --> 00:56:01,490
For the first time in my life,

931
00:56:01,492 --> 00:56:03,492
I'm realizing he's
not our father.

932
00:56:03,494 --> 00:56:06,328
He is, Julie. He
always has been.

933
00:56:06,330 --> 00:56:07,330
I know.

934
00:56:07,331 --> 00:56:09,531
I keep telling myself that,

935
00:56:09,533 --> 00:56:12,968
but now it's like he
could just disappear

936
00:56:12,970 --> 00:56:15,738
and it'll be like it was
before he came along,

937
00:56:15,740 --> 00:56:17,139
like we were never a family.

938
00:56:17,141 --> 00:56:18,707
Don't say that!

939
00:56:20,276 --> 00:56:23,412
I've always been able
to count on you.

940
00:56:23,414 --> 00:56:25,547
I'm sorry.

941
00:56:25,549 --> 00:56:27,249
I'm trying.

942
00:56:30,153 --> 00:56:32,221
I'm really trying.

943
00:57:00,617 --> 00:57:02,117
[ Maria laughs ]

944
00:57:26,309 --> 00:57:29,845
Well, I'm amazed that you have
the strength to pursue this

945
00:57:29,847 --> 00:57:31,480
after what you've been through,

946
00:57:31,482 --> 00:57:33,315
losing your only child.

947
00:57:33,317 --> 00:57:35,217
She's not my only child.

948
00:57:35,219 --> 00:57:37,986
I'm sorry. I meant your only...

949
00:57:37,988 --> 00:57:40,422
I'm just saying it's a
beautiful thing,

950
00:57:40,424 --> 00:57:41,590
what you're trying to do,

951
00:57:41,592 --> 00:57:43,559
but it is a big lift.

952
00:57:43,561 --> 00:57:45,394
It's not gonna be all Kumbaya.

953
00:57:45,396 --> 00:57:47,329
I've been trying to
tell him that.

954
00:57:47,331 --> 00:57:48,964
John, you're a developer, right?

955
00:57:48,966 --> 00:57:52,367
You see a piece of property,
you go, "what's this cost?"

956
00:57:52,369 --> 00:57:53,669
Then you pull a few strings.

957
00:57:53,671 --> 00:57:55,170
You bend a few rules.

958
00:57:55,172 --> 00:57:56,738
A year later, the job is done.

959
00:57:56,740 --> 00:57:58,474
The government's not like that.

960
00:57:58,476 --> 00:58:01,944
In politics, you have to hold a
very high standard of
low expectations.

961
00:58:01,946 --> 00:58:03,045
Let's say the
county's behind it,

962
00:58:03,047 --> 00:58:04,746
but some jerks in the
legislature,

963
00:58:04,748 --> 00:58:06,215
they're opposed to it,

964
00:58:06,217 --> 00:58:08,083
because they... they got some
kind of pet project.

965
00:58:08,085 --> 00:58:09,852
Yeah, or the
legislature's in favor,

966
00:58:09,854 --> 00:58:12,855
but the division of
budget kills it.

967
00:58:12,857 --> 00:58:16,158
I mean, I don't want to say
anything, but...

968
00:58:16,160 --> 00:58:17,160
Say it.

969
00:58:19,429 --> 00:58:21,029
We both know

970
00:58:21,031 --> 00:58:23,332
you made one or two
enemies along the way.

971
00:58:23,334 --> 00:58:27,636
Come on. It's not like I'm
trying to build a strip club.

972
00:58:27,638 --> 00:58:29,571
I know.

973
00:58:29,573 --> 00:58:33,075
Like I said, it's a
beautiful thing.

974
00:58:33,077 --> 00:58:34,943
I'm just saying.

975
00:58:39,148 --> 00:58:42,351
John: No family should have to
endure what we did.

976
00:58:42,353 --> 00:58:43,752
This is just a no-brainer.

977
00:58:43,754 --> 00:58:45,487
You've got people around here
taking their kids

978
00:58:45,489 --> 00:58:47,122
to a hospital that's...
it's a nightmare.

979
00:58:47,124 --> 00:58:50,058
I mean, you gotta be able to
raise money to fix that, right?

980
00:58:50,060 --> 00:58:52,094
Woman: I wish I had better
news to tell you,

981
00:58:52,096 --> 00:58:55,664
but unfortunately the numbers
just don't add up.

982
00:58:55,666 --> 00:58:58,400
We've looked at it from
several different angles.

983
00:58:58,402 --> 00:59:00,068
And this is what it is.

984
00:59:00,070 --> 00:59:02,971
So say you need 120
million to build this.

985
00:59:02,973 --> 00:59:05,541
130 by the time you're done.

986
00:59:05,543 --> 00:59:08,110
So to issue bonds for this,

987
00:59:08,112 --> 00:59:11,613
you need donations of at
least 25 million.

988
00:59:11,615 --> 00:59:13,015
Right, yeah.

989
00:59:13,017 --> 00:59:15,317
Unfortunately, our study shows

990
00:59:15,319 --> 00:59:17,553
that you'd be lucky to raise 10.

991
00:59:17,555 --> 00:59:19,888
10? This is the richest
part of the country.

992
00:59:19,890 --> 00:59:21,957
Trouble is you have
no donor base.

993
00:59:21,959 --> 00:59:24,126
This is a county facility.

994
00:59:24,128 --> 00:59:26,828
People feel like they've done
more than their share

995
00:59:26,830 --> 00:59:28,397
by just paying their taxes.

996
00:59:28,399 --> 00:59:30,299
What about, um, a
corporate sponsor?

997
00:59:30,301 --> 00:59:33,068
Maybe, if you let them put
their name on it.

998
00:59:33,070 --> 00:59:34,303
They might contribute something.

999
00:59:34,305 --> 00:59:35,504
Exactly.

1000
00:59:35,506 --> 00:59:37,105
Maria's name is going on it.

1001
00:59:37,107 --> 00:59:39,308
What? Maria's name is
going on it.

1002
00:59:39,310 --> 00:59:41,043
Right.

1003
00:59:42,278 --> 00:59:45,080
Well, I wish you luck.

1004
00:59:48,618 --> 00:59:50,752
Thank you for your time.

1005
00:59:54,123 --> 00:59:56,792
All right, um...

1006
00:59:59,062 --> 01:00:02,764
Maybe... maybe you should
rethink this.

1007
01:00:02,766 --> 01:00:04,333
Rethink what?

1008
01:00:04,335 --> 01:00:05,834
Aren't you listening to
anything anyone has to say?

1009
01:00:05,836 --> 01:00:07,202
What's the point?

1010
01:00:07,204 --> 01:00:08,403
What's the point?

1011
01:00:08,405 --> 01:00:09,605
They're just saying no.

1012
01:00:09,607 --> 01:00:11,840
Why do you think that is?

1013
01:00:14,510 --> 01:00:16,311
[ Sighs ]

1014
01:00:16,313 --> 01:00:17,779
You want to quit?

1015
01:00:31,361 --> 01:00:33,495
Thanks for dinner. It was good.

1016
01:00:34,964 --> 01:00:36,665
John.

1017
01:00:36,667 --> 01:00:39,034
Yeah?

1018
01:00:40,403 --> 01:00:42,270
I want to be involved.

1019
01:00:44,807 --> 01:00:46,408
With the hospital.

1020
01:00:46,410 --> 01:00:47,876
I want to help.

1021
01:00:50,546 --> 01:00:52,814
You don't... you don't need me?

1022
01:00:52,816 --> 01:00:55,017
You want to do it all...
all by yourself?

1023
01:00:55,019 --> 01:00:57,586
What are you talking about?
I have Bruce.

1024
01:01:06,062 --> 01:01:07,396
Jesus.

1025
01:01:08,765 --> 01:01:10,499
She was my daughter, too!

1026
01:01:12,068 --> 01:01:15,804
You are not the only one
who feels hurt!

1027
01:01:15,806 --> 01:01:18,740
You have three other children!

1028
01:01:18,742 --> 01:01:21,443
Do you even care what
they're going through?

1029
01:01:33,423 --> 01:01:34,856
Say something.

1030
01:01:41,264 --> 01:01:43,231
[ Crying ]

1031
01:01:47,537 --> 01:01:50,706
I can't do this anymore.

1032
01:01:50,708 --> 01:01:54,576
I can't... I can't be strong
for you anymore.

1033
01:01:54,578 --> 01:01:56,445
I can't do it.

1034
01:01:56,447 --> 01:01:58,447
[ Fragments crunching ]

1035
01:02:17,934 --> 01:02:20,602
Maria: Adults are so weird.

1036
01:02:23,873 --> 01:02:28,076
Mom told me it scares her when
dad doesn't talk to her,

1037
01:02:28,078 --> 01:02:31,379
because when she was little,
her mother would get mad

1038
01:02:31,381 --> 01:02:35,951
and wouldn't talk to her for
weeks, literally.

1039
01:02:37,220 --> 01:02:39,955
But she doesn't want
dad to know that,

1040
01:02:39,957 --> 01:02:41,857
because she thinks it
would freak him out

1041
01:02:41,859 --> 01:02:43,358
or piss him off or something.

1042
01:02:46,863 --> 01:02:50,098
But maybe dad doesn't
talk sometimes

1043
01:02:50,100 --> 01:02:54,102
because actions speak
louder than words.

1044
01:03:05,648 --> 01:03:07,382
John?

1045
01:03:07,384 --> 01:03:09,551
Yeah, it's me.

1046
01:03:13,656 --> 01:03:16,391
Where have I been?

1047
01:03:16,393 --> 01:03:18,960
I don't know.

1048
01:03:18,962 --> 01:03:21,296
I don't know either.

1049
01:03:22,765 --> 01:03:24,299
I'm sorry.

1050
01:03:26,769 --> 01:03:29,037
I'm sorry, too.

1051
01:04:24,293 --> 01:04:29,030
How long have you been
building hospitals?

1052
01:04:29,032 --> 01:04:31,666
Well, gee, it's been
about 17 years now.

1053
01:04:31,668 --> 01:04:33,034
Yeah? More or less.

1054
01:04:41,777 --> 01:04:44,512
Ready?

1055
01:04:44,514 --> 01:04:45,881
Uh, I don't know.

1056
01:04:45,883 --> 01:04:47,716
I really don't know about this.

1057
01:04:47,718 --> 01:04:48,718
Want to cancel?

1058
01:04:48,719 --> 01:04:49,719
Maybe.

